Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
merge_model_timing(25.10)                            merge_model_timing(25.10)

Name
       merge_model_timing  -  Merges extracted timing models (ETM) for various
       analysis views into a single output

Syntax
       merge_model_timing

       [-help]

       [-keep_separate_arc]

       -library_file <string>

       -mode_group <string>

       -modes <string>

       [-outfile <string>]

       [-pin_cap_tolerance <float>]

       [-tolerance <float>]

       Merges extracted timing models (ETM) for various analysis views into  a
       single output.

       The  merge_model_timing  command  should be the last command in the run
       script. Also, this command should be run separately in a Tempus session
       when a design is not loaded.

       When the DRV values are different in the  libraries  that  are  merged,
       then Tempus saves the worst value of the DRV with a warning message.

       If  the  DRV  values are not equal, the greater value is stored for the
       following:

              * Minimum transition

              * Minimum capacitance

              * Minimum fanout

       The smaller value is stored for the following, in case of unequal DRVs:

              * Maximum transition

              * Maximum capacitance

              * Maximum fanout

              * Fanout load

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -keep_separate_arc
              Enables creating separate timing arcs with respective modes.

       -library_file <string>
              Specifies input library files that are to be merged.

       <->modes <string>
              Specifies the mode names required for merging the libraries. The
              number of mode names should be equal to the number of input  li-
              braries.

       -mode_group string
              Specifies the name of the mode group.

       -outfile string
              Specifies  the  name  of  the merged library output file. By de-
              fault, the output file name is merge.lib.

       -pin_cap_tolerance float
              Specifies the pin capacitance  tolerance  for  making  tolerance
              comparison for library merging.

       -tolerance <float>
              Specifies  the  tolerance  value for making tolerance comparison
              for library merging.

Examples
              * The following command merges  library  files  model1.view1.lib
                and model1.view1.lib.ref into a single output file:

                merge_model_timing       -library_file       "model1.view1.lib
                model1.view1.lib.ref"

                -modes "v1 v2" -mode_group v1_v2

Related Information
              * See "Extracting Timing Models" in the Innovus User Guide.

              * write_model_timing

              * compare_model_timing

